Assignment - Getting and Cleaning Data Course Project

● Merges the training and the test sets to create one data set
First of all, the datasets were downloaded from the link in the assignment instruction page. Then, we loaded the necessary datasets and combined rows and columns to build a complete dataset.

The following are the datasets used to create the complete table:
1. train/X_train.txt
2. test/X_test.txt
3. train/subject_train.txt
4. test/subject_test.txt
5. train/y_train.txt
6. test/y_test.txt
7. features.txt

● Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement
Among all the columns, we filtered out the columns where there's no either "mean" or "std" in the name.

● Uses descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set
As 1-6 are ambiguous activity names, we replced those numbers with the names in the "activity_labels" text file to make the names more descriptive.

● Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names
To make viewers easily understand what the dataset is about, we labeled all the columns from the names in the "features" text file.

